e larger than acidophils with less granulation","Acidophils are less granulated than basophils","Chromophobe cells are small with minimal cytoplasm","Basophil cells are smaller than chromophobe cells","Acidophil cells have minimal cytoplasmic content"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe anterior pituitary contains three distinct cell types with specific morphological features:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChromophobe cells\u003C/strong\u003E are small, round to polygonal cells with minimal cytoplasm and few secretory granules\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAcidophil cells\u003C/strong\u003E are large cells with abundant cytoplasm and numerous secretory granules\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBasophil cells\u003C/strong\u003E are larger than acidophils and less heavily granulated\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding these cellular characteristics is important for identifying different cell types in histological examination and understanding their functional roles in hormone production.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Chromophobe cells are small with minimal cytoplasm and few secretory granules","Acidophil cells are large with abundant cytoplasm and secretory granules","Basophil cells are larger than acidophils and less heavily granulated"],"references":["Hormone supply to the pituitary gland: A comprehensive investigation of female\u2011related tumors (Review). Int J Mol Med. 2022 Oct;50(4):122. doi: 10.3892/ijmm.2022.5178. Epub 2022 Aug 10. PMID: 35946461; PMCID: PMC9387558","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Colle